    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect sequence number validation in PDCP reordering window check\n\n### Summary\nThe PDCP sequence number validation logic in `pdcp_data_ind` contained an incorrect bounds check that always evaluated to true due to unsigned arithmetic. This caused PDUs with valid sequence numbers to be incorrectly discarded, leading to data loss in the PDCP layer.\n\nThe issue occurred when checking if a received PDU's sequence number was within the acceptable reordering window. The condition `pdcp_p->last_submitted_pdcp_rx_sn - sequence_number >= 0` was always true for unsigned values, making the entire validation logic flawed.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder network conditions with out-of-order PDCP PDUs, observe that valid PDUs within the reordering window are being incorrectly discarded with log messages:\n```\n\"discard PDU, out of sequence\"\n```\n\nTraffic analysis shows missing data segments that correspond to sequence numbers that should have been accepted but were dropped due to the faulty validation.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/PDCP_v10.1.0/pdcp.c`: Fixed unsigned arithmetic comparison in reordering window validation (lines 830-831)\n"
}